git init - We start GIT in the folder where the project is

git status - List a current repository status with list of modified or added files

git rm - Delete a file from the repository

git clone - We clone the github repository

git add. - We add all the files for the commit

git commit -m "Text identifying the commit" - We do the first commit

git push - upload to repository

git add * .txt - We add all files with the specified extension

git commit -a -m "Text identifying the commit" - Add and Load the changes made to the HEAD

git push --tags - Upload a tag

git log - Show the commit logs

git reset - Reset current HEAD to the specified state

git checkout - Switch branches or restore working tree files

git diff - Show changes between commits, commit and working tree, etc





